💎 All clear glass on this sherlock, showing off the clean execution of the skills involved in making this piece. The carb is sealed onto the piece at a tangential angle. A tangent (or tangential angle) is a mathematical explanation for lowering a line, line segment, or a ray, (Who remembers geometry class?) onto a circle, where there is only one point of interception along the egde of said circle. The result is that the incoming air will spin the smoke as it passes through the piece. The benefit? Ambient air mixing with your smoke cools down your hit so you can medicate harder, faster. The advantage of spinning spoke as opposed to a regular carb, is that centrifugal force helps to disperse thermal energy. This enables you to take bigger hits without coughing your lungs out. SCIENCE!  Additionally, the indents on the right side are conveniently placed for the user's fingers, making the piece functional on an #ergonomic, AND on an #aerodynamic level💎 ~Available as of 8/21/2019~

⚠️Attention friends/family⚠️ A few days after my engagement earlier this month my soon to be mother-in-law fell near fatally ill due to diabetes and had to be airlifted to UVA hospital in Charlottesville. She is alive and recovering now but unfortunately they had to take her foot to save her. As one can imagine she has a long recovery ahead of her, which also means there will be some very large hospital bills as well. In an effort to help relieve my family of some of the financial burden all profits from my glass sales through my big cartel account for the foreseeable future will be donated to her recovery fund. Things have finally calmed down enough for me to get back in the studio and get to work on a few things, and  I will be posting this red white and blue bubbler for sale later this evening. The link to my shop will be in my bio and a link to her go-fund-me account will be posted soon. Thank you all so much in advance 🙏✌️♥️
-TyCo
